Rata Blanca (White Rat in English) is a heavy metal band from Argentina formed in 1986.
The guitarist Walter Giardino replaced Osvaldo Civile in V8 for a little time, and left the band when his songs were rejected. 
His friend Roberto Cosseddu, bassist of Kamikaze, helped him to record a demo tape with those songs. 
The drummer Gustavo Rowek, who had also left V8 a short time before, declined his projects with Civile and joined Giardino. 
The session musicians Rodolfo Cava (singer) and Yulie Ruth (bass player) completed the line-up that recorded the demo.
